OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe Garden of France       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwithers in worst drought   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Loire Valley is known as "the      
OL,6, Garden of France". But the garden is   
OL,7, withering.                             
OL,9,FFrance's worst drought since records   
OL,10,Fbegan has turned lush vegetation into  
OL,11,Farid fields of brown crops, shrivelling
OL,12,Funder what is now the fourth heatwave  
OL,13,Fof the year.                           
OL,15,FIn Vincent Favreau's vegetable farm,   
OL,16,Fwhere he produces food for a hundred   
OL,17,Ffamilies in the area, the parched earth
OL,18,Fhas stunted the growth of the cabbages.
OL,19,FHis potato plants are burnt out,       
OL,20,Fproducing just half the crop of a      
OL,21,Fnormal year.                           
